ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Testing of fixation and smooth pursuit: Broken up smooth pursuit
Testing of fixation and smooth pursuit: Square wave jerks on fixation
Testing of fixation and smooth pursuit: Downbeat-nystagmus on fixation
Testing of fixation and smooth pursuit: Gaze evoked-nystagmus on horizontal testing
Testing of fixation and smooth pursuit: Gaze evoked-nystagmus on vertical testing
Testing of fixation and smooth pursuit: Ophthalmoparesis on horizontal gaze
Testing of fixation and smooth pursuit: Ophthalmoparesis on vertical gaze
Testing of fast saccades: Slowing of saccades
Testing of fast saccades: Hypometric saccades
Testing of fast saccades: Hypermetric saccades
Testing of visual function: Impaired visual acuity (loss of visual acuity <0.6 for binocular sight in distance testing)
Reported Abnormalities: Spontaneous cramps(without physical exercise)

Notes: To be automatically calculated in the electronic database
